text: One thing I appreciate about the Amish is that they actually physically look like Medieval peasants. You would assume they'd look like regular guys and the entire Medieval peasant look is something invented by artists in the 19th century, but no. They actually look like peasants.

When Emperor Hirohito was growing up in an environment very similar to the orphanage from Death Note which L was raised in with brutal amounts of studying he still had to do fencing, wrestling, swimming, sports. The Japanese, more than anyone else, know what it means to be white.
Puyi was also a very good fencer and proficient at orienteering even though he later had to lie about it IIRC

You can actually find Brezhnev's diaries published and many excerpts are online and they are all wonderful. Zero concern about ideology or communism. Just a series of notes on swimming, hunting, playing dominoes, massage, watching television, haircuts, trying to lose weight, etc.
Just a man with a job that allowed him to travel a lot and stay at nice summer resorts.

More factoids from Dmitry Galkovsky but even the Duchy of Courland had colonies in Africa and the Caribbean at one point. Most people have probably never heard it even existed. Also per Galkovsky's analysis one single province of China was worth as much as the entirety of Africa.
